history.content: I took it in the spring and really enjoyed it. The exam is very reasonable, somewhat easy if you do all previous exams. I took it without 127 and did well. Taking 189 early means you could do research or take 194/graduate courses that required 189 early. I'd recommend the spring version since it has higher HKN rating.

For context, I have taken 16b and 126, but not 127, expected graduation 2024. The main concern I have is I heard that cs189 in fall is more theoretical, and in spring is more application-based, and the curve is also nicer in fall, given that I learn a concept best when I know what exactly is going on in terms of math, and I'm interested in research on areas of CV or neural network, I also perform better with harder homework and easier exams(because I have exam anxiety), in this case, should I take cs189 this spring or ee127 this spring + 189 this fall(I can't take 189 and 127 together coz schedule conflict). Are there any benefits to take 189 earlier?Any thoughts? Thanks!
history.subject: Should I take cs189 this spring or fall 2022
